        <abstract> 
<p>CD is unable to give the desired information relating to embryology of the Vertebrata. He advises the procuring of F. M. Balfour’s <hi rend="italic">Comparative embryology</hi>, in two volumes [1880–1], which he believes to be the most valuable biological work in many years.</p> 
            <p>Hopes to find time to read VLS’s essays.</p> 
<p>Discussion of the problem of naming species. [See <hi rend="doubleUnderline">13568</hi>.]</p> 
        </abstract>
